=Liaozhai zhiyi 聊齋誌異=
==Literature==
===Translations===
* [[Herbert A. Giles]]: Strange Stories from a Chinese Studio. New York: Paragon Book Gallery, 1908 [[http://www.archive.org/details/strangestoriesf01gilegoog|pdf]]
* Irmgard Grimm and Reinhold Grimm: Höllenrichter Lu: Chinesische Gespenster- und Fuchsgeschichten. Kassel: Erich Röth-Verlag, 1956
* [[Gottfried Rösel]]: Zwei Leben im Traum: 67 Erzählungen der Bände fünf bis acht aus der Sammlung Liao-dschai-dschi-yi. Zürich: Verlag die Waage, 1989
===PhD Dissertations===
* Marlon Kau Hom: The Continuation of Tradition: A Study of Liaozhai zhiyi by Pu Songling (1640-1715). University of Washington, 1979
* [[Allan Barr]]: Pu Songling and Liaozhai zhiyi: A Study in Textual Transmission, Biographical Background, and Literary Antecedents. Oxford University, 1983
* Luo Hui: The Ghost of Liaozhai: Pu Songling's Ghostlore and its History of Reception. University of Toronto, 2009 [[https://tspace.library.utoronto.ca/bitstream/1807/17472/1/Luo_Hui_200903_PhD_thesis.pdf|pdf]]
===Monographs===
* [[Judith T. Zeitlin]]: Historian of the Strange: Pu Songling and the Chinese Classical Tale. Stanford: Stanford University Press, 1993
* [[Chun-shu Chang]] and [[Shelley Hsueh-lun Chang]]: Redefining History: Ghosts, Spirits, and Human Society in P'u Sung-ling's World, 1640-1715. Ann Arbor: The University of Michigan Press, 1998
===Articles===
* [[Chun-shu Chang]] and [[Shelley Hsueh-lun Chang]]: P'u Sung-ling and His Liao-chai chih-i: Literary Imagination and Intellectual Consciousness in Early Ch'ing China. Renditions 13 (1980): 60-81
* [[Allan Barr]]: A Comparative Study of Early and Late Tales in Liaozhai zhiyi. HJAS 45.1 (1985): 157-202
* [[Allan Barr]]: Disarming Intruders: Alien Woman in Liaozhai zhiyi. HJAS 49.2 (1989): 501-517